        "title": "feat: add context-engine host capability requirements",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add optional context-engine host requirement metadata and assertion helpers\n- reject unsupported generic CLI hosts before running context engines requiring pre-prompt assembly\n- declare native Codex/Pi embedded host support and document the contract\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/context-engine/host-compat.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.test.ts src/agents/harness/v2.test.ts src/agents/harness/selection.test.ts extensions/codex/index.test.ts` — passed 8 files / 149 tests.\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` — passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions` — passed.\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check` — passed after regenerating `docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256`.\n- `git diff --check` — passed.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior addressed:** Context engines can declare agent-run host requirements; generic CLI hosts reject engines requiring pre-prompt assembly, while the built-in Pi harness advertises support for `assemble-before-prompt` and passes the host compatibility assertion.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw PR worktree on macOS, after patch commit `62287f2782`, using the real source entrypoints with `node --import tsx`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a terminal smoke script importing `createPiAgentHarness`, `assertContextEngineHostSupport`, and `buildGenericCliContextEngineHostSupport`; the script created a real context-engine object requiring `assemble-before-prompt`, asserted generic CLI rejection, then asserted Pi harness acceptance using the built-in harness capabilities.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output:\n\n```text\ngeneric-cli rejected: Context engine \"proof-engine\" cannot run operation \"agent-run\" on CLI backend \"test-cli\". Missing host capabilities: assemble-before-prompt. Required capabilities: assemble-before-\npi-harness accepted: pi bootstrap,assemble-before-prompt,after-turn,maintain,compact,runtime-llm-complete\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Unsupported generic CLI host combinations fail closed before launch with a missing-capability error; the built-in Pi harness now advertises the documented pre-prompt assembly capability and satisfies the same host check.\n- **What was not tested:** A live LLM-backed native Codex/Pi conversation turn was not run from this PR branch; the smoke proof exercises the real host compatibility source path without sending a model request.\n",
